Chimera - Observatory Automation System
=======================================

Installation:

Before installing Chimera, install the following packages using the standard way
on your distribution.

python-numpy python-dev python-numpy libusb-dev swig saods9 sextractor astrometry.net

python-sqlalchemy (it doesn't install automatically for me)

developer extras:

 nosetests

documentation extras:

epydoc (it doesn't install automatically for me)

After that,

$ cd <uncompressed_chimera_dir>
# su
# python setup.py install 

setup.py must be run as root user to install Chimera on a system-wide basis.

Windows install:

Install Tortoise SVN
Use SVN Checkout and download the code.
If you use the normal (not develop) install, after checking out do 

python setup.py install

The following has happened:

No locale packages or download links found for pywin32==210
error: Could not find suitable distribution for Requirement.parse('pywin32==210')

PH suggestion:

Na página http://sourceforge.net/projects/pywin32/files/, procure pelo
Build 210 e baixe o executavel apropriado ao Python instalado na
máquina e execute-o. Depois disso rode o setup.py do Chimera
novamente. Deve ser o suficiente.

just like the unix version

